Bernard van der Linde of UP Tuks heads for the tryline during the 2022 Varsity Cup Final between Maties and UP Tuks. BackpagePix/Shaun Roy JOHANNESBURG -Â Tuks are the 2022 Varsity Cup rugby champions. The men from the capital scored the winning try towards the end of their tight match against the University of Stellenbosch at the Danie Craven Stadium. The 29-23 victory gave Tuks their fifth title overall. They had to come from behind to defend the crown they won last year. Fullback Stefan Coetzee attacked from deep, going through the Maties defensive line to set up Bernard van der Linde for the winning score. With this win, Tuks join Stellenbosch as the two most successful teams in the tournament, with five titles each.